name: Transfusion Blues
author: Johnny Cash
lyrics:
Early one morning while making the rounds

He said, "Willy Lee, your name is not Jack Brown
You're the dirty hack that shot your woman down"
Said, "Yes, oh yes, my name is Willy Lee
If you've got a warrant, just read it to me"
Shot her down because she made me slow
I thought I was her daddy, but she had five more
When I was arrested, I was dressed in black
Put me on a train and they took me back

Just before the jury started out
I saw that little judge commenced to look about
In about five minutes, in walked the man

Verdict read "in the first degree"
I hollered, "Lordy, Lordy, have a mercy on me"
The judge he smiled as he picked up his been
Ninety-nine years in the San Quentin pen
Ninety-nine years underneath that ground
I can't forget the day I shot my woman down
Come all you gotta listen unto me
Lay off that liquor and let that transfusion be

name: Second Lovers Song
author: Townes Van Zandt
lyrics:
Youâre wakin' next to me,    tears splash 'cross the sun.
   You whisper soft to me     that I ain't the only one
   To breathe your yella'(or: raven) hair,    caress your bosom fair.
   Do you think I really care?    Do you think it matters?
   What do your feelin's mean?    Do you think I'd love you more,
   If you stood pure and clean    of those you'd known before?
   Would your words be sweeter then,    upon November's wind?
   If you began again,    could your smile be softer?
   Would your eyes more brightly shine? Would your laughter be so tender,
   If you'd been only mine for as long as you remember?
   I don't want tears from you,    don't build your love on shame.
   All that we've done is through    and all we can do remains.
   My lady can't you see,    I love not jealously?
   But for all you are to me    and all you'll be tomorrow.

name: Why Shes Acting This Way
author: Townes Van Zandt
lyrics:
Like silence she stands

They'll soon start t'believe

Oh what it all goes to show
it ain't my job to say

why she's actin' this way

if you're sure that it's done

take your cup full of fire

'Cause I got no place to be
and I ain't far from home
